{"id": 15, "ts": 1778780948.7354167, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_1", "message": "Here is a consolidated view of what we know about each candidate across the selection criteria, followed by the gaps that still exist:\n**Candidate\u202fA**\n- *Technical / cognitive*: anticipates dangerous situations, sees complex connections, excellent spatial vision.\n- *Leadership*: very good leadership qualities.\n- *Negative traits*: sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized, unfriendly.\n- *Missing*: No explicit statements on reliability, responsibility, stress handling, calmness under pressure, decision\u2011making speed, teamwork/communication, or long\u2011term development.\n**Candidate\u202fB**\n- *Reliability / responsibility*: very conscientious (suggests reliability).\n- *Technical / cognitive*: good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills.\n- *Stress handling*: handles stress very well.\n- *Teamwork / communication*: makes nasty remarks about colleagues, can be grumpy and uncooperative \u2013 clear red flags for crew cooperation.\n- *Missing*: No explicit information on overall responsibility, decision\u2011making, or long\u2011term development.\n**Candidate\u202fC**\n- *Reliability / responsibility*: known to be 100\u202f% reliable.\n- *Technical / cognitive*: understands complicated technology, can make correct decisions quickly.\n- *Calmness under pressure*: keeps calm in a crisis.\n- *Teamwork / communication*: creates a positive atmosphere with his crew (strong crew\u2011cooperation signal) but has difficulty communicating ideas and is regarded as egocentric.\n- *Professional development*: not very willing to further his education.\n- *Overall*: strong on reliability, technical competence, and crew atmosphere; weaknesses lie in communication style and willingness to develop further.\n**Candidate\u202fD**\n- *Reliability / responsibility*: takes responsibility seriously.\n- *Technical / cognitiv